<p>

<a href="dev_view.jsp?id=64311&start=5">Older</a>
</p>

 
<h1>Backflagging</h1>
	<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><FONT face="Times New Roman">As you know, when a guild gains or loses members, they often find themselves dedicating a large amount of time re-playing content that they have long since completed in order to gain access to zones for newer members.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>During our Community Summit this last summer, and in many subsequent discussions, we have heard the recurring desire to find a way to ease the frustrations associated with this backflagging.<?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" /><o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><o:p><FONT face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><FONT face="Times New Roman">While the issue is not as simple as removing flags altogether (we feel flags are necessary for the zones they are currently attached to), we have looked into ways that we can reduce the frustrations of backflagging and feel that we have arrived at a fair and equitable solution, which is detailed below.<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><o:p><FONT face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; tab-stops: .25in; mso-layout-grid-align: none"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><FONT face="Times New Roman"><SPAN style="mso-tab-count: 1">-&nbsp;</SPAN>A new implementation of the 85/15 rule will be introduced into Planes of Power zones including the Plane of Time.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>This should resolve the outstanding problems that occur from time to time with the current 85/15 implementation.<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; mso-layout-grid-align: none"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><FONT face="Times New Roman">- The new 85/15 will also be introduced for the locked zones in Gates of Discord.<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><FONT face="Times New Roman">- An alternate means of flagging guild mates for locked content in Planes of Power and Gates of Discord will be implemented that will allow you to flag raid members for the zone you are in by completing raid content within that zone.&nbsp;<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</SPAN></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><FONT face="Times New Roman"><SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes"></SPAN></FONT></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><FONT face="Times New Roman"><SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes"></SPAN>The implementation varies slightly from zone to zone to fit the story and nature of the zone, but in general will involve killing a raid target within that zone, looting an item, and completing a single group quest to change that item into a zone flag.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>This only applies to zones that don't already have a single group task or system to gain access.<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><o:p><FONT face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><FONT face="Times New Roman">We will be opening threads on the forums for you to discuss these proposed changes and to gather your feedback on whether you feel this will hg!elp to resolve the current problems with backflagging.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Please join the threads on our EQ forums and let us know your thoughts on these proposed changes.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>We hope to have these on the test server shortly after Thanksgiving and Live after proper testing.<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><o:p><FONT face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><FONT face="Times New Roman">Thanks and Happy Thanksgiving!</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><o:p><FONT face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><FONT face="Times New Roman">The EverQuest Team.<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>


